getName

public abstract java.lang.String getName()
Returns:
Title of example.

create

public abstract void create()
Create the world geometry for each test. Any custom initialization for a test should go here. Called immediately after initialize(), which handles generic test initialization and should usually not be overloaded.

createWorld

public void createWorld()
Overload this if you need to create a different world AABB or gravity vector

initialize

public void initialize()
Should not usually be overloaded. Performs initialization tasks common to most examples:
  • Resets input state
  • Initializes member variables
  • Sets test settings
  • Creates world, gravity and AABB by calling createWorld() - overload that if you are unhappy with defaults
  • Sets up and attaches listeners
  • Sets up drawing
  • Sets camera to default or saved state
  • Calls create() to set up test

step

public void step()
Take a physics step. This is the guts of the simulation loop. When creating your own game, the most important thing to have in your step method is the m_world.step() call.
